When i read it, it makes me feel bad. I didnt do anything, and yet, that self dislike ive been trying to move out of, the good in myself ive been trying to think of, the anxieties of talking to people, how i talk, everything about me, just when i am better, it happens again.

Its like every time im getting better and happier and healthier, i get a message from that person. last friday was very hard on me in particular about this. just when i felt like i was able to move forward it happens again.

guess today was meant to not be my day. ugh… im so so tired of dealing with this situation that ive been the past 5 months now. i just want to move on. it escalated again a few minutes ago. not my doing. im so tired.

Again, apologies for getting into this again, but i had held off from speaking about it for long enough, and it takes me a while to process things. 
I know now what friendship is. And sometimes, it’s just enjoying another person’s presence.

Levels, and expectations that were never once communicated other than yelling at me for doing something they considered was “outside those expectations” like not talking constantly to them, is just extremely unhealthy. Friendships arent a contract.

Because i had done that as a kid, but didnt as an adult, i was incapable of fulfilling the needs and expectations of a “best friend” to that person. Thus, they no longer saw me as a friend.

There are boundaries to friendship, sure. I get that. But having complex rules-

A little more detail in the issue that had happened to me that im comfortable enough to share:
Essentially, to the person, a “best friend” was expected to be a priority, talking to them all the time, every day, every hour, and if i hadnt done that, i was toxic

yeah
I lost friends because of this, unfortunately, to some people it isnt enough to be a friend. Thats what i learned. But then again, they werent really the best people out there since i was expected to act a certain way with them https://t.co/o2GHsaH6ZI

I think of it as evidence that “oh, because this happened i am not a good friend or person” and it’s scary.

I dunno. Sorry for clogging your timelines, just thinking about some stuff.

i dont like confrontation, i dont like causing rifts in friendships. But that’s what did happen in the situation the past few months/weeks. Its scary because even though i know i havent done anything, of course, when im anxious, i think i did.
Im afraid of making things awkward between people. Im afraid of killing conversations. It’s really, really terrifying to me.

It’s stupid ya know? I should be reaching out to people more now that i know my friends have supported me

But today, im scared. Im anxious.

Im afraid of being the issue.

I wanted to be more confident reaching out to people this year. But of course, now im scared it seems like all i do is just ask things of people. Because i was told that.

It makes me anxious. It makes me afraid to reach out. That’s why ive been much more inactive lately.

Some days are worse than others, of course. Like today. 

I just wish it wasnt so hard.

The situation ive dealt with the past few months/weeks has also heightened my anxiety and made me far more wary of how i talk to people

I am moving on but im so, so scared.
Im scared of talking to acquaintances.
Im scared of talking to friends.

Im scared of being the problem

Anxiety literally prevents me from doing stuff such as:

-saying hi to people
-asking people a question or something
-interacting with people in any way due to fear of being weird

*Making friends
